Project Title: Packaged Foods Management System
1. Overview
The Packaged Foods Management System is designed to manage operations for packaged 
food products, including product catalog, stock monitoring, order processing, and compliance 
tracking. It provides functionalities for product registration, batch tracking, expiry alerts, billing, 
and reporting, all implemented using an MVC architecture.
This design supports both Java (Spring MVC) and .NET (ASP.NET Core MVC) frameworks.
The system consists of five primary modules:
1. Product & Batch Management
2. Customer Management
3. Order & Billing Management
4. Inventory & Expiry Tracking
5. User Authentication & Authorization
2. Assumptions
• The system will be deployed locally using MySQL or SQL Server.
• Role-based access will be implemented for Admin, Store Manager, and Customer 
roles.
• ORM tools (Hibernate for Java, Entity Framework Core for .NET) will handle 
database interactions.
• The UI will be responsive and optimized for mobile and desktop users.
• Expiry alerts will be triggered based on batch dates.
3. Module-Level Design
3.1 Product & Batch Management Module
Purpose: Handles product registration and batch details.
• Controller:
o ProductController
▪ addProduct()
▪ updateProduct()
▪ getProductDetails()
▪ getAllProducts()
• Service

o ProductService
▪ Business logic for product lifecycle.
• Model:
o Product Entity 
▪ Attributes: 
▪ productId (PK)
▪ name
▪ category
▪ price
▪ status (ACTIVE, INACTIVE)
• Batch Entity:
o Attributes: 
▪ batchId (PK)
▪ productId (FK)
▪ manufactureDate
▪ expiryDate
▪ quantity
3.2 Customer Management Module
Purpose: Manages customer profiles and purchase history.
• Controller:
o CustomerController
▪ addCustomer()
▪ updateCustomer()
▪ getCustomerDetails()
• Service:
o CustomerService
▪ Handles customer lifecycle.
• Model:
o Customer Entity 
▪ Attributes: 
▪ customerId (PK)
▪ name
▪ email
▪ phone
▪ status (ACTIVE, INACTIVE
3.3 Order & Billing Management Module
Purpose: Processes orders and billing.
• Controller:
o OrderController
▪ placeOrder()
▪ getOrderDetails()
▪ generateBill()
• Service:
o OrderService
▪ Handles order lifecycle and billing.
• Model:
o Order Entity 
▪ Attributes: 
▪ orderId (PK)
▪ customerId (FK)
▪ orderDate
▪ totalAmount
3.4 Inventory & Expiry Tracking Module
Purpose: Tracks stock levels and expiry alerts.
• Controller:
o InventoryController
▪ updateStock()
▪ getStockReport()
▪ checkExpiry()
• Service:
o InventoryService
▪ Calculates stock availability and expiry alerts.
• Model:
o Inventory Entity 
▪ Attributes: 
▪ inventoryId (PK)
▪ batchId (FK)
▪ quantity
3.5 User Authentication & Authorization Module
Purpose: Provides secure login and role-based access.
• Controller:
o AuthController
▪ login()
▪ registerUser()
▪ logout()
▪ getUserProfile()
• Service:
o AuthService
▪ Handles authentication and authorization.
• Model:
o User Entity 
▪ Attributes: 
▪ userId (PK)
▪ username
▪ password (hashed)
▪ email
▪ role (ADMIN, STORE_MANAGER, CUSTOMER)
4. Database Schema
Product Table
CREATE TABLE Product (
productId INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
name VARCHAR(100),
category VARCHAR(50),
price DECIMAL(10,2),
status ENUM('ACTIVE','INACTIVE')
);
Batch Table
CREATE TABLE Batch (
batchId INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
productId INT,
manufactureDate DATE,
expiryDate DATE,
quantity INT,
FOREIGN KEY (productId) REFERENCES Product(productId

);
Customer Table
CREATE TABLE Customer (
customerId INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
name VARCHAR(100),
email VARCHAR(100),
phone VARCHAR(15),
status ENUM('ACTIVE','INACTIVE')
);
Order Table
CREATE TABLE Orders (
orderId INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
customerId INT,
orderDate DATE,
totalAmount DECIMAL(10,2),
FOREIGN KEY (customerId) REFERENCES Customer(customerId)
);
User Table
CREATE TABLE User (
userId INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
username VARCHAR(50) UNIQUE,
password VARCHAR(255),
email VARCHAR(100),
role ENUM('ADMIN','STORE_MANAGER','CUSTOMER')
);
5. Local Deployment Details
• Install MySQL or SQL Server, JDK 17/21/24 or .NET SDK 8.0.
• Deploy using Apache Tomcat (Java) or Kestrel (.NET).
• Steps: 
1. Clone repository from GitHub/Bitbucket.
2. Set up database schema.
3. Configure application.properties or appsettings.json.
4. Build and run application.
6. Conclusion
The Packaged Foods Management System provides a modular MVC design for managing 
products, batches, customers, and inventory with expiry alerts. It ensures secure role-based 
access and efficient local deployment
